National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) have uncovered 58.5 grams of cocaine and 13.9 grammes of heroine concealed in the palace of a prominent traditional ruler in Anambra State. On Monday, Femi Babafemi, the spokesman, said investigation had commenced to unravel how the drugs were hidden. He quoted the Anambra State Commander, Muhammadu Idris, as saying the palace security guards are assisting in tracing the dealer behind the consignment. Also, Hassan Bishi Taiwo was arrested at the Murtala Mohammed International Airport (MMIA) in Lagos. The suspect was caught with three parcels of cocaine tucked in a false bottom created in his suitcase. Taiwo was intercepted last Friday after arrival at about 1:30 pm. He flew in aboard Ethiopian Airlines “We discovered another ticket on him while our findings also show that he has been plying his criminal trade through some Middle East countries”, NDLEA said. Similarly, narcotics officers attached to a courier company in Lagos discovered 500grammes of cocaine going to the United Arab Emirates (UAE) and concealed inside the walls of packed cartons containing clothes. Another courier firm found one kilogramme of cannabis inside cream bottles going to UAE, 500grammes of ketamine hidden in artifacts going to the United States, and 480grammes of methamphetamine going to China. Video: VIDEO: Three parcels of cocaine concealed in the false bottom of a traveling bag by a drug trafficker being unraveled by an NDLEA officer at the Lagos airport.@ndlea_nigeria @FemiBabafemi @_mahad_ pic.twitter.com/sRu6YjLfZv — NDLEA NIGERIA (@ndlea_nigeria) March 8, 2021 